Attached to this report, a simple viewer  that shows how to handle events on
a GVT tree. The example does not only test that (I have reused another simple
viewer I have done for tracking memory leaks).

See the piece of code:

		BridgeContext ctx = svgComp.getBridgeContext();
		Document document = svgComp.getSVGDocument();
		Element elt = document.getElementById("rect");
		GraphicsNode gn = ctx.getGraphicsNode(elt);
		gn.addGraphicsNodeMouseListener
		    (new GraphicsNodeMouseAdapter() {
			public void mouseClicked(GraphicsNodeMouseEvent evt) {
			    System.out.println("Hello");
			}
		});

If people are interesting in seeing other documents using this program - please
remove that part.
